<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-218-310  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 218 310.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Digital Review  April 24 1989 v6 n16 p13(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>VigiLAN lets users monitor LAN in real-time from home.andO;(Experdata's performance monitoring unit) (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Gianatasio, David.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Experdata Inc. (product introduction).andO;Product:   Experdata VigiLAN (Network analyzer) (product introduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionPerformance MeasurementNetwork MonitorsCSMA-CDCommunications EquipmentFunctional CapabilitiesNetwork Management.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>VigiLAN Lets Users Monitor LAN in Real-Time from HomeandM;BLOOMINGTON, Minn.andP;  -- Experdata has introduced a protocol-independent,real-time performance monitoring unit for carrier-sense multiple-eccesscollision detect (CSMA/CD) networks.andP;  Company officials said the new offeringboast communications functions for local or remote reporting of networkactivity.andM;The monitor, dubbed VigiLAN, is intended for &quot;large data communicationnetwork management&quot; applications, officials said.andM;VigiLAN can be controlled remotely or locally via standard RS-232-C seriallinks from a non-dedicated, PC-based central station.andM;VigiLAN can report on such network activity as throughput, collision rates,and the number and type of erros with time-stamped peak values.andM;VigiLAN provides station statistics for as many as 256 stations automaticallyranked according to network-bandwidth utilization.andP;  With it, network managerscan identify stations that transmit but never receive data, and vice versa.andM;In addition, the product provides node connection reports detailing thenumber of frames and bytes transmitted to and from a specific stations, andidentifies stations causing errors.andM;VigiLAN, available now, is priced at $5,200.andM;Experdata Inc. is located at 10301 Toledo Ava S., Bloomington, MN 55437,(612)831-2122.andO;</TEXT></DOC>